# Cognify-AI Backend – Environment Variables

Copy this file to `.env` and fill in your values.

```dotenv
# ====================
# Server
# ====================
PORT=4000
NODE_ENV=development

# ====================
# Database (PostgreSQL)
# ====================
DATABASE_URL=postgresql://postgres:postgres@localhost:5432/cognify_ai

# ====================
# Authentication
# ====================
JWT_SECRET=dev-secret-change-in-production-min-32-chars
JWT_EXPIRES_IN=7d
REFRESH_TOKEN_SECRET=dev-refresh-secret-change-in-production-min-32-chars
REFRESH_TOKEN_EXPIRES_IN=30d

# ====================
# AI Providers
# ====================
# Set DEFAULT_AI_PROVIDER to auto-select, or leave empty for auto-detect.
# Valid: gemini | openai | anthropic | openrouter | groq | together | deepseek | codezen | openai_compatible
DEFAULT_AI_PROVIDER=gemini

# --- Free / free-tier providers (recommended to start) ---
GROQ_API_KEY=              # https://console.groq.com — free tier
GEMINI_API_KEY=            # https://aistudio.google.com — free tier
OPENROUTER_API_KEY=        # https://openrouter.ai — free models available
TOGETHER_API_KEY=          # https://api.together.xyz — signup credits
DEEPSEEK_API_KEY=          # https://platform.deepseek.com

GEMINI_MODEL=gemini-2.5-flash

# --- Optional paid providers ---
OPENAI_API_KEY=
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=

# --- Generic OpenAI-compatible API (LM Studio, Ollama proxy, local servers) ---
OPENAI_COMPATIBLE_API_KEY=
OPENAI_COMPATIBLE_API_URL=   # e.g. http://localhost:1234/v1/chat/completions
OPENAI_COMPATIBLE_MODEL=     # e.g. llama-3.2-3b-instruct

# --- CodeZen / Codzen gateway (backend only — never expose in frontend) ---
CODEZEN_API_KEY=
CODEZEN_API_KEY_2=
CODEZEN_KEY2_MODELS=gpt-5-mini,gpt-5-nano,claude-opus-4-7,gemini-3.1-flash-lite-preview
CODEZEN_API_URL=https://llm-gateway.codzen.ai/v1/chat/completions
CODEZEN_MODEL=

# ====================
# Security / CORS
# ====================
CORS_ORIGIN=http://localhost:3000

# ====================
# Rate Limiting
# ====================
RATE_LIMIT_WINDOW_MS=60000
RATE_LIMIT_MAX=60
AI_RATE_LIMIT_MAX=20
AI_REQUEST_TIMEOUT_MS=120000

# ====================
# Optional Redis
# ====================
REDIS_URL=
```

## Quick start (free tier)

1. Sign up at [Groq Console](https://console.groq.com) and create an API key.
2. Add `GROQ_API_KEY=gsk_...` to `backend/.env`.
3. Optionally set `DEFAULT_AI_PROVIDER=groq`.
4. Restart the backend: `npm run dev --workspace=backend`.

Test configured providers:

```bash
curl http://localhost:4000/api/ai/providers
```
